                            <comment id="13601814" author="stack" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 23:36:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 as long as you can make the alias work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why call it something wah like &lt;del&gt;META&lt;/del&gt;?  We have the notion of &apos;system tables&apos; now...  We should name them w/ same convention if possible.  I suppose there is &lt;em&gt;acl&lt;/em&gt; which would fit this category.  What tables did Jesse add if any in his patch?  System tables being with a dot?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13601844" author="enis" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 23:59:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, we have system tables starting with &quot;.&quot;, &quot;-&quot;, &quot;_&quot;, respectively in META, ROOT, and acl. Agreed that we should select one and stick with it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740150" author="stack" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 20:31:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolve.  Fixed by namespaces introduction of system tables.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740153" author="stack" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 20:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Namespaces renamed .META. as hbase:meta where hbase is the &apos;hbase&apos; system table.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
